      "writtenOn": "2026-07-21T09:11:56Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "To the discussion:\n\nrdeOpID has a separate description in the spec (`5.3.25 rdeOpID PLDM data type`). I wonder if we should create a separate type for it:\n```\nuint16 OperationIdentifier \n\nNumeric identifier for the Operation. Operation identifiers with the most significant bit set \n(1b) are reserved for use by the MC when it instantiates Operations.  Operation identifiers \nwith the most significant bit clear (0b) are reserved for use by the RDE Device when it \ninstantiates Operations in response to commands from other protocols that it chooses to \nmake visible via RDE. The value 0x0000 is reserved to indicate no Operation. \n```\n\nI also wonder what should we do about Device/MC flag.\n\n```\nstruct pldm_rde_op_id {\n    uint16_t id: 15;\n    uint16_t direction : 1;\n};\n```\n\nOr should we at least add something like `PLDM_RDE_MC_INITIATED_OPERATION (1\u003c\u003c15)`?",
      "revId": "dee825176f5f2766aff6d85c0b7cd8537e686796",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": false,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "e0cc70a5_0c1375a9",
        "filename": "include/libpldm/rde.h",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 645,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002838
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-07-22T04:23:37Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Add PLDM_RDE_MC_INITIATED_OPERATION (1\u003c\u003c15) and PLDM_RDE_OPERATION_ID_NONE",
      "parentUuid": "bff44d63_6b27150f",
      "revId": "dee825176f5f2766aff6d85c0b7cd8537e686796",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
